Same question. In general too, you shouldn't pass arguments to test since people shouldn't be calling them separately. The only exception would be helper functions, i.e.

  def _test_foo(self, use_bar):
      # lots of common stuff here
      if use_bar:
          # bar-specific stuff
      # lots more common stuff here

  def test_foo_with_bar(self):
      self._test_foo(use_bar=True)

  def test_foo_without_bar(self):
      self._test_foo(use_bar=False)

If that makes sense?
